    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9800" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὥρη</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">season</span>,
          esp. the spring, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.468</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.51</span></i>; and in pl.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">seasons</span> of the year, <i><span class="en">Od.
            10.469</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.107</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; Διὸς ὧραι</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 24.394</span></i>; then the fitting, right <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">time</span>
          (like <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καιρός</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δόρποιο, ὕπνου, γάμου</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            15.126</span></i>; with inf., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὕδειν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 11.373</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            πρὶν ὥρη</span> (‘before 't is time’), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν
            ὥρῃ, εἰς ὥρᾱς</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
          9.135</span></i>.—Personified, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ὧραι</span>, the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Hours</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-la" lang="lat">Horae</span>), door -
          keepers of Olympus and goddesses of the seasons, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.749</span></i> ff., <i><span class="en">Il. 8.393</span></i>, <i><span class="en">433</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
